Whereas the Minister of Citizenship and Immigration has given the notice required under section 18 of the Citizenship Act, (Act), as it read on May 27, 2015, to the person named in the annexed schedule (person) of the Minister’s intention to make a report under section 10 of the Act, as it read on May 27, 2015;

 

Whereas that person requested that the Minister refer the case to the Federal Court and the Minister referred the case to the Court;

 

Whereas the Federal Court has decided that that person obtained Canadian citizenship by false representation or fraud or by knowingly concealing material circumstances; 

 

Whereas on September 13, 2016, a copy of the report that the Minister intended to make to the Governor in Council was sent to that person who was given ninety days to provide submissions as to why his citizenship should not be revoked;

 

Whereas counsel for that person made submissions, including those regarding the personal circumstances of that person, which were carefully considered by the Minister;

 

Whereas the Governor in Council has carefully considered the report from the Minister made pursuant to section 10 of the Act, as it read on May 27, 2015, and the submissions made by that person and received by the Minister, and concurs with the reasons set out in the report;

 

 

 

